MALACAÑANG MANILA BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE PHILIPPINES

PROCLAMATION NO. 766

RESERVING FOR SETTLEMENT SITE PURPOSES FOR THE AETAS OF FLORA, APAYAO, CERTAIN PARCEL OF LAND OF THE PUBLIC DOMAIN AND DECLARING THE SAME OPEN FOR DISPOSITION TO THE ACTUAL OCCUPANTS THEREOF, SITUATED AT BARANGAY BALASI, MUNICIPALITY OF FLORA, PROVINCE OF APAYAO, ISLAND OF LUZON.

Upon recommendation of the Secretary of Environment and Natural Resources and by virtue of the powers vested in me by law, I, FIDEL V. RAMOS, President of the Philippines, do hereby reserve for settlement site purposes for the Aetas of Flora, Apayao, certain parcel of land of the public domain and declaring the same open for disposition to the actual occupants thereof, pursuant to the provisions of the Public Land Act, as amended, situated at Barangay Balasi, Municipality of Flora, Province of Apayao, Island of Luzon, which parcel of land is more particularly described as follows:

Plan Swo- 133204-000263

A parcel of land (Plan Swo-133204-000263) situated at Barangay Balasi, Municipality of Flora, Province of Apayao, Island of Luzon. Bounded on the NE., along lines 1-2-3-4-5-6 by alienable and disposable area, Block No. III, LC Map No. 2311; on the SW., along lines 7-8-9 and SE., along lines 9-10-11 by Timber land; on the SW., & NW., along lines 11-12-13-14 by Timber land; on the NW., along lines 14-15-16-1 by Tamalunog Creek. Beginning at a point marked “1” of plan being S., 82 deg., 05’W., 2301.11 m. from BLLM No. 43, “Allig Plains Public Land Subdivision, Pls-93, Apayao, thence:

